# Security Standards

Treat every input and request as hostile.

## Always

- Authenticate session
- Authorize permission/role **on the server** for every mutation and sensitive read
- Validate with schemas (Zod) at boundaries
- Scope data by org/tenant/store — never trust client-sent org IDs alone
- Sanitize/escape output where XSS is possible

## Never trust

Client body, query params, headers, cookies contents as authorization proof, or hidden form fields for permissions.

## Secrets

No secrets in client bundles. Service-role keys only on server. Never commit `.env` credentials.

## Destructive / admin

Confirm intent in UI; enforce again on server. Audit sensitive changes when the domain requires it.
